rent per Visa Bulletin · Medical and character clearances"},{"label":"India backlog reality","value":"Indian-born EB-2/EB-3 applicants often wait years after I-140 approval for priority date to become current. Monitor Visa Bulletin monthly.","warning":true},{"label":"Key authority","value":"USCIS · Department of Labor (PERM) · Department of State (Visa Bulletin/NVC)"},{"label":"After approval","value":"Receive green card; maintain residence; eligible for citizenship after qualifying period (typically 5 years)."}],"eligibility":[{"criterion":"Qualifying EB category or family relationship","met":true},{"criterion":"Employer sponsorship / PERM (EB-2/3)","met":false,"note":"PERM adds 12–18 months"},{"criterion":"I-140 approved","met":false},{"criterion":"Priority date current (Visa Bulletin)","met":false,"note":"Check monthly bulletin"},{"criterion":"I-485 or consular processing eligible","met":false},{"criterion":"Medical exam completed","met":false},{"criterion":"No serious inadmissibility","met":true}],"redFlagsBanner":"If priority date not current, I-485 cannot be filed—monitor Visa Bulletin and maintain lawful status meanwhile.","redFlags":[{"title":"Priority date not current","description":"Client expects green card but Visa Bulletin shows years of backlog.","fix":"Monitor Visa Bulletin; maintain H-1B/status; set realistic timeline","severity":"Very common"},{"title":"PERM recruitment issues","description":"DOL audits or inadequate recruitment advertising.","fix":"Ensure PERM compliance; experienced immigration attorney for PERM","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Status gap during wait","description":"Fell out of status while waiting for priority date.","fix":"Maintain valid non-immigrant status throughout wait","severity":"High"},{"title":"Job change during PERM/I-140","description":"Changed employer before I-140 approved 180+ days.","fix":"Understand AC21 portability rules; may need new PERM","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Incorrect EB category","description":"Filed EB-3 when EB-2 qualifications exist or vice versa.","fix":"Assess education/experience for optimal category","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Medical inadmissibility","description":"Health grounds not addressed.","fix":"Complete medical early; consult on waivers if needed","severity":"Medium"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee green card?","a":"No. Multi-step process with DOL, USCIS, and visa availability. Never promise approval or timeline."},{"q":"How long for Indians EB-2?","a":"Check current Visa Bulletin—often many years backlog. Dates move monthly."},{"q":"What is PERM?","a":"Labor certification proving no qualified US workers available—required for most EB-2/EB-3."},{"q":"Can spouse work during wait?","a":"Depends on status—H-4 EAD, L-2, or EAD with pending I-485 if eligible."},{"q":"What is priority date?","a":"Date PERM filed or I-140 receipt—determines place in queue per Visa Bulletin."},{"q":"EB-1 vs EB-2?","a":"EB-1 for extraordinary ability/multinational managers—no PERM. EB-2 typically needs PERM unless NIW."},{"q":"What is NIW?","a":"National Interest Waiver—EB-2 without PERM if work benefits US national interest."},{"q":"Family-based options?","a":"I-130 through US citizen/LPR relatives—preference categories have own backlogs."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Lawful permanent residence (green card) via employment sponsorship (EB-1/2/3/5) or family petition (I-130). Multi-step process involving PERM, I-140, priority date, and I-485 or consular processing."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Qualifying job offer/sponsor (EB) or qualifying family relationship · PERM for most EB-2/3 · Priority date current per Visa Bulletin · Medical and character clearances"},{"q":"What is India backlog reality for this service?","a":"Indian-born EB-2/EB-3 applicants often wait years after I-140 approval for priority date to become current. Monitor Visa Bulletin monthly."},{"q":"Important note on India backlog reality?","a":"Indian-born EB-2/EB-3 applicants often wait years after I-140 approval for priority date to become current. Monitor Visa Bulletin monthly."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"USCIS · Department of Labor (PERM) · Department of State (Visa Bulletin/NVC)"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Receive green card; maintain residence; eligible for citizenship after qualifying period (typically 5 years)."},{"q":"Is Qualifying EB category or family relationship required?","a":"Qualifying EB category or family relationship is typically required."},{"q":"Is Employer sponsorship / PERM (EB-2/3) required?","a":"PERM adds 12–18 months"},{"q":"Is I-140 approved required?","a":"Assess whether I-140 approved is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"Is Priority date current (Visa Bulletin) required?","a":"Check monthly bulletin"},{"q":"Is I-485 or consular processing eligible required?","a":"Assess whether I-485 or consular processing eligible is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"Is Medical exam completed required?","a":"Assess whether Medical exam completed is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"Is No serious inadmissibility required?","a":"No serious inadmissibility is typically required."},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"2–10+y — Category & country dependent"},{"q":"What is the Government fee?","a":"USD $2,000+ — Multiple forms over process"},{"q":"What is the Our approval rate?","a":"85% — ~78% benchmark"},{"q":"What is the Required docs?","a":"22 — + employer docs for EB"},{"q":"What is the Consultancy fee?","a":"See fee tab — + govt & legal"},{"q":"What if the client has Priority date not current?","a":"Monitor Visa Bulletin; maintain H-1B/status; set realistic timeline"},{"q":"Why is Priority date not current a problem?","a":"Client expects green card but Visa Bulletin shows years of backlog."},{"q":"What if the client has PERM recruitment issues?","a":"Ensure PERM compliance; experienced immigration attorney for PERM"},{"q":"Why is PERM recruitm