,{"q":"Important note on Interview reality?","a":"Most decisions made in short interview. Officer assesses intent, ties, and credibility—not document volume alone."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"US Department of State — Embassy/Consulate in India"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Visa foil in passport; officer at port of entry decides admission length (often up to 6 months). No work permitted."},{"q":"Is Valid passport required?","a":"6+ months validity recommended"},{"q":"Is Clear temporary purpose required?","a":"Tourism, family, business meeting—not employment"},{"q":"Is Strong ties to India required?","a":"Job, business, property, family"},{"q":"Is Proof of funds for trip required?","a":"Bank statements, ITR, sponsor letter"},{"q":"Is DS-160 completed accurately required?","a":"Must match interview answers"},{"q":"Is No prior visa fraud required?","a":"No prior visa fraud is typically required."},{"q":"Is Interview appointment booked required?","a":"Via ustraveldocs.com"},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"1–4w — After interview; slot wait extra"},{"q":"What is the Government fee?","a":"USD $185 — MRV non-refundable"},{"q":"What is the Our approval rate?","a":"72% — ~58% industry benchmark"},{"q":"What is the Required docs?","a":"8 — + purpose-specific"},{"q":"What is the Consultancy fee?","a":"See fee tab — + govt only"},{"q":"What if the client has Weak ties to India?","a":"Employment letter, business registration, property, family dependencies"},{"q":"Why is Weak ties to India a problem?","a":"Unemployed, no assets, young single applicant with vague purpose."},{"q":"What if the client has 214(b) — immigrant intent signals?","a":"Clear temporary purpose; return date; no employment intent"},{"q":"Why is 214(b) — immigrant intent signals a problem?","a":"Mentions working in USA, long stay without reason, or visiting fiancé without clear plan."}],"compliance":["Client service agreement and consent on file before D